This paper deals with the computation of channel capacity in the context of fingerprinting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) used in fingerprinting. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of non-binary alphabets, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications.
